 That install applies to "Video Kid" © 1992 Gremlin
 
 That install requires WHDLoad and RawDIC to be in the path.
 Both can be found in the whdload package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select Expert as
 installation mode.
 
 You need 0.5 MB ChipMem and 1.0 MB OtherMem.
 You can quit the game by pressing F10 (key can be changed with
 Tooltype "QuitKey=")
 
 
 if you have problems with this installation please report them via
 the Bug-Report-Form which can be accessed on 
 http://www.whdload.de or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de
 
 for full WHDLoad package and other installs refer to:
     http://www.whdload.de
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/
 
 Version 2.1 (09.01.2021) done by JOTD:
 - help skips level when joypad controls isn't active (issue #0004942)

 Version 2.0 (13.12.2020) done by JOTD:
 - joypad controls (issue #0004900)
 - adapted to whdload v17
 - gfx glitches fixed on fast machines (racing the beam issues)
 - quitkey on 68000 machines
 - fixed keyboard read routine
 - protection completely skipped
 - trainer x3 (adapted from MrLarmer hardcoded trainer)
 - using 512k chip memory instead of 1MB
 - now using rawdic islave instead of patcher imager
 - levelskip with help (or fwd+green)
 - manual added
 
 Version 1.0 (01.10.1998) done by Mr.Larmer/Wanted Team:
 - protection removed
 - fast decrunching files (Byte Killer highly optimized)
 
 Thanx to:
 -  Chris Vella for original disk images.

joypad controls:

* blue button: bomb (SPACE)
* play: pause (P)
* rev+fwd: quits current game (ESC)
* rev+fwd+yellow: quits to workbench (QUITKEY)
* fwd+green: skips current level (HELP)

Supported version: SPS2555
